                                       <p>Bottom part of mixing arm</p>
                                    </entry>
                                 </row>
                              </tbody>
                           </tgroup>
                        </table>
                     </p>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
            <ol id="substeps_ehw_4qs_lcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Starting at the discharge slide, undo the screw connections and remove all
                     floor liner segments.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Fit the mixer floor with the new floor liner segments.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ul id="ul_p1y_qqs_lcc">
                        <li>Starting from the discharge, align the floor liner segments.</li>
                        <li>Underpin any bumps at the fixation points.</li>
                        <li>Perform the fixation of the floor liner segments to the right and left
                           of the discharge, and then continue progressively until complete.</li>
                        <li>Make sure that there is a parallel gap between the individual floor
                           liner segments and the discharge slide.</li>
                     </ul>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Replacing steel sheet or hard cast iron outer wall segments:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Undo the screw connections on the outer wall of the mixer, and remove the
                     outer wall segments.</li>
                  <li>Align the new outer wall segments on the outer wall of the mixer, and screw
                     them into place.</li>
                  <li>Make sure that there is no offset on the contact edges.</li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Replacing wear parts for the discharge slide seal:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Unscrew the floor wear liner of the discharge slide.</li>
                  <li>Replace the parts, and screw them back on.</li>
               </ul>
               <p>
