            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Replacing a mixing trough scraper:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Remove the mounting (4) with the clamp (5), and remove the scraper.</li>
                  <li>Install the new scraper (3) and lightly fix into place with the clamps (5) and
                     mountings (4).</li>
                  <li>Adjust the scraper (3) so that there is a gap of 1-2 mm from the wear liner of
                     the discharge slide (1).</li>
                  <li>Tighten the clamps with the fastening screws.</li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" id="note_nxq_gss_lcc">
                  <p>Inspect all scrapers at regular intervals, and readjust if necessary.</p>
               </note>
